race.comment: Tough. ZOUSINGER (3) resumes and is right up to this if presented on song. She's placed 2.3 fresh and placed in a recent Mornington jumpout. Has a handy 2kg claim and likes to position on pace. SMASHING ACTION (10) resumes and has won 1/2 fresh. She was busting to win before the spell and owns an easy trial win from Murray Bridge. She will use the low barrier and has decent claims. QUIK RHAPID (1) was in the money two starts back at Bordertown but was unable to repeat the effort at Mt Gambier when he jumped slowly and was caught wide. Peaks today and won't know himself dropping back from 68s to a 56. He races forward, and the 3kg claim brings him right into it. SUNBURNT (8) is fourth-up and has been freshened 40 days. She's been within range at Warrnambool her last two and has the blinkers applied for the first time. The inside gate should advantage and she also deserves plenty of consideration.
